# Plaid Slide Design — Cursor rule

This rule auto-attaches the **plaid-slide-design** skill whenever you edit
slide-related files. The skill enforces the Plaid Deck Design System and
blocks customer/host brand colors from leaking into `.slide-root`.

**Canonical skill:** [`.claude/skills/plaid-slide-design/SKILL.md`](../../.claude/skills/plaid-slide-design/SKILL.md)
**Cursor mirror:** [`.cursor/skills/plaid-slide-design/SKILL.md`](../skills/plaid-slide-design/SKILL.md)
**Pipeline loader:** [`scripts/scratch/utils/slide-design-skill.js`](../../scripts/scratch/utils/slide-design-skill.js)

## Hard rules (summary — read SKILL.md for full text)

1. **Slides are Plaid-branded only.** Inside `.slide-root`, never use customer
   primary/CTA hex (e.g. `#034F54`, `#5BA63C`, `#388E3C`) or customer heading
   fonts (`Huntington Serif`, host Google Fonts).
2. **Source of truth** = `templates/slide-template/brand-design-briefs/`
   (`DECK_DESIGN_SYSTEM.md`, `DECK_TEMPLATES.md`, `DECK_COMPOSITION.md`) plus
   `colors_and_type.css`, `slide.css`, `pipeline-slide-contract.css`. Do not
   invent palette or typography outside these files.
3. **Customer name in `post-slides` prompt is for partnership copy only**, not
   permission to use customer palette inside `.slide-root`.
4. **Pick one** of T1–T11 per slide; set `data-slide-template="T#"` on
   `.slide-root`.
5. **Approved palette** = `--plaid-ink-900` (#022544), `--plaid-teal-500`
   (#42F0CD), navy/cream/holo backgrounds, `#E8E4D8` cream text.
6. **Bundled logos only**: `assets/logos/plaid-horizontal-{white,dark,holograph}.png`.
   Never invent SVG, icon grids, or "PLAID" text.

## Pipeline integration

The pipeline injects this skill into every slide LLM call automatically
([`scripts/scratch/scratch/post-slides.js`](../../scripts/scratch/scratch/post-slides.js)).
When you hand-edit slide HTML, follow the same rules so build-qa scanners
(`slide-invented-color`, `slide-shell-chrome`, `slide-canvas-size`,
`slide-narration-drift`) stay green.

## Recovery

If slide-tier QA fails after edits:

```bash
npm run pipe -- slide-fix [RUN_ID]
```
